13080029[=]ustv[=]WhiteHZ[=]2010-08-01 00:09:40[=]标题：Greatest Couples in Teleplay(draft) --my own version of the top 10 couples[=]Reference material: IMDB （the original version with Picture:http://www.douban.com/note/83375549/） First of all, I’d like to say I haven’t watched Teleplay that long a time. These are only my opinion from those plays I’ve watched. #10 Kat Gardener & Darryl Van Horne (Eastwick 2009) Darryl is handsome, mysterious, and kind of dangerous. The kind of guy can attract every woman, he makes you want him but also hate him. Even when Darryl first moved to the little town, Kat still seeing Chad, she has a feeling on him. But the more Kat and her friends investigate bout him, more questions come. Who’s Darryl? What’s he doing here? And what does he want from me? But Darryl knows everything, and sometimes makes a little chaos to Kat. Even though Darryl make a move on all three ladies in the play. Obviously, he likes Kat the most. At the end of season 1, K&D end up being together. #9 Olivia Dunham & Peter Bishop (Fringe 2008-) Can two people from different worlds be together? In this case, this is not a metaphor. Because Peter actually comes from parallel universe. The relationship between Olivia and Peter is delicate, from only colleague to friends to great friends both save each other’s lives several times, then finally to couple. The episode about the musical in season two is a short version of their relationship. At the end of season 2, Dr. Bishop and others rescue peter back to their own universe, Olivia was trapped in the other world. Can Olivia and Peter be together in Season 3? #8 Ned & Chuck (Pushing Daisies 2007-2009) Comparing to lots of porn-like relationship: you met, you in, you out, you never see each other again. Ned and Chuck’s love story is definitely a fairytale. Everything between them is so sweet. There are others first kiss and first love. Years later, like Prince Charming wake up Sleeping Beauty, Ned gave Chuck a second life by touching her. But Ned can never touch Chuck in any way, or she will die again, forever. There can’t be any physical contact, no hug, and no kiss. When it come by love, other things just seem not so important. #7 Chuck Bartowski & Sarah Walker (Chuck 2007-) Sexy CIA agent and computer nerd who accidentally know all the government secrets, there’s love from the first sight, but they just can’t be together. When Chuck told Sarah he likes her, she lie to him, saying it’s just her job. She can say whatever she want, but the feeling won’t go away, seeing these two struggle in the relationship, I can’t help but thinking, love is not that hard, just told the truth. But when Sarah finally get over all those “just job” thoughts and planning to escape from CIA with Chuck to begin their own life, Chuck didn’t go. Their story continues in the coming season. #6 Chandler Bin & Monica Geller (Friends 1994-2004) Unlike Rachel and Ross, Chandler and Monica’s story is much less complicated. Awkward sociality Chandler afraid of commitment, control freak Monica always date the wrong guys either too old or too young. At the early season, no one foresee they will get marry. Although there are some hints, like when Carol delivery the baby in the hospital, Chandler says to Monica, “If we’re 40 and still both not married, what do you said you and I get together.” And some others I can’t remember them all. They did have some history, Chandler call Monica fat then Monica accidentally cut his toe tip down and something like that. After they slept together at Ross’s second wedding, the relationship between them becomes serious: Chandler moving in, then propose, then the wedding. After they find out they can birth a baby themselves, they chose to adopt one, which giving their story a happy ending. #5 Sid Jenkins & Cassie Ainsworth (Skins Season 1-2 2007-2009) To this couple, I actually gave it lots of thoughts. This is the only teenagers couple makes into my top 10. Skins is a meaningful, the play totally destroy our traditional opinion about teenagers. It talks about serious teenagers’ problem in a realistic way, and how those trouble kids deal with their lives. Sid always live under the shadow of his friend Tony, Tony was good at everything, most-importantly, he has Michelle, the girl Sid has a crush on for a long time. Cassie has her own problem, Eating Disorder. After Sid eventually man up to Tony, he realize Cassie is the one he likes and likes him. During, they go through some serious misunderstanding. Cassie move out town but move back for Sid. After one of their best friends Chris die, Cassie Ran away from everything past and move to New York. After high school end, after talking to Tony, Sid know he made a mistake letting Cassie go so he fly to NY also, looking for Cassie. Meeting Cassie is the greatest thing happen in Sid’s life. Before that, Sid is nothing but a total loser. Cassie gave Sid the courage to love and grow up, and rather take the risk to chase the one he loves. At the end of Season 2, Sid passes the diner room Cassie works, leaving us an unanswered question: have Sid found her? But I believe he did. #4 Hank Moody & Karen (Californiacation 2007-) California, always so sun shining, story here is also like it. Hot and easy get burn. Hank once was a successful writer for writing “God Hates Us All”, but recently he could write anything.  Why? I will say he’s lost his muse. We know hank and Karen always love each other, no matter what excuse Karen telling herself, eventually she end up with Hank. There are just way too many troubles to getting them two together: Karen’s marriage, all kinds of affairs around Hank. This is not Karen’s fault. Passion of course makes feel good, but after a certain age, women more likely tending to settle down with family. Karen is not young any more, don’t even mention wanting to give her daughter better home. I remember when Karen told Hank, “you are not in love with me, you just in love of the feeling of you love me”. First heard it, I thought maybe, Karen is right, guys like Hank rather stay single, for all the pretty ladies around. But as the story goes on, I find out Hank really love Karen too much, he is loyal to her, and always be honest to her. How many couples can really do this. The affairs can’t blame him all, it’s not his fault ladies thought he’s irresistible attracted, and something Hank just being sweet for doing them a favor however lead to the sex part. And the sex with Mia, before it, Hank doesn’t know she is just 16 years old. At the end of Season 3, just before finally deciding move back to New York, Hank told the truth about Mia lead to a big fight. Hope these love birds can make up in next season. #3 Luke Danes & Lorelai Gilmore (Gilmore Girl 2000-2007) I know the most important main line in this play is the mother-daughter bonding, but the romance story between Luke and Lorelai is also very impressive. Many viewers hope Lorelai end up with Christopher Hayden, Rory’s dad. I don’t. I know Lorelai is the one told Christopher to chase his dream years ago, but he cares too little, so many years without contacts is not a father should do, no need to mention he marry another women. When he asked Lorelai to marry him, I thought, it’s too little too late. Oppositely, Luke is always there, when Lorelai need help, or been through something horrible. Besides, her favorite diner is Luke’s, according to Lorelai’s Words, Luke’s coffee is the best coffee ever. I can’t count how many time they two fight, about some tiny little thing or something big like when Lorelai was dating Luke’s nephew. Then Lorelai won’t go to Luke’s Diner, for a while, before she release he can’t live without Luke’s coffee. But we all know what she really can’t live without is Luke, besides he is the soul-mate, he is also her good friend she can talk to, laugh with and rely on. When Luke told Larelai he’ve kept a small newspaper about Lorelai in his wallet for years when they first met, Lorelai was touched, so was I. Just like Lorelai’s mom said, Lorelai’s life is too dramatic. After their engagement, she found out Luke got a daughter but didn’t tell her, then break up with him. By the end of Season 7 (last season), he found out the big party Luke threw for Rory, and how much he care for not only her, but her daughter too, he is the one she want to be with. In all 7 season, Rory change boyfriends three times. And at the ending she chose to follow her dream as a reporter and turning down Logan’s purpose. In comparing, Luke and Lorelai got a deeper relationship, even by the time she was seeing someone else, Luke’s still there supporting her. That’s means a lot. The last scene at season 7 is in Luke’s diner, just like the pilot of season 1, seven years of stories end, in a happy way. #2 Mr. Big & Carrie Bradshaw (Sex and the City 1998-2004, plus the movie 2008) To a both successful and pretty woman like Carrie, every guy wants her, however, she chose the hardest achieved one-- Mr. Big. Sex and the City is well know for its strong feminism. “At the first time in Manhattan women have the equal power as men, and can have sex like men.” So says Samantha. And that’s what these four fabulous women do, men comes and leaves. Big didn’t, he just kept coming again and again in Carrie’s life. Basically, they met, then met again, fall in love, break up, then fall in love again, then break up again, then Big marry another women and later divorce her for Carrie, then Carrie fall for Aidan, Big fight her back, Carrie move to London with another man, Big fly to there and commit to her and move back to New York. If this is a fairytale, the princess will quit long time ago waiting the Prince Jerk. But Carrie is a strong woman, after hurting so many time by big, when he’s back, she chose him, even means to hurt her again. Still remember that scene vividly in the pilot: “Carrie: have you ever been in love?  Big: Abso-Fucking-lutely.” That’s the time Carrie first realize after so many years so many dating, she never know what loving someone feel like. Viewers said Big can’t exist in our real life, because he’s too perfect, is he? Maybe except from his anti-feminism, and his arrogant and self-center. He won’t make major scarification for others, not even for Carrie. When he’s back with his new fiancé, He breaks Carrie heart into pieces. But when Carrie met him outside his wedding, all she said is “Your bride is so pretty”. In years, a nice boyfriend finally happens to Carrie, Aidan. Big’s  back too, Disturbing Carrie’s short happy days, because Carrie of course will chose him. At the last season, Big chase Carrie to London, they met in the hotel, Carrie was crying, they hug and kiss, Big brought her back with him. In the movie, Sex and the City, Big and Carrie finally get married and their happy ever after. The relationship between Big and Carrie is Complicated, not easy to understand. The real problem is how much will you give up love someone. The play is one of the greatest ones ever, and it begin a new era for Female plays, so many plays later we can still see the more or less affection of Sex and the City. (The movie 2 got pretty bad criticism though, I still looking forward to it. ) #1 Ross Geller & Rachel Green (Friends 1994- 2004) I watched Friends many, many times. So much wanted to say, but this is about the love story between Ross and Rachel. Too much touching scene in Friends about them two. We always ask what’s true love, watching Ross and Rachel, I know this is. There’s so obvious these two belong to each others, Chandler Monica Phoebe and Joey know it, any other people they’ve dated know it, and every viewer knows it. They have been through too much together, they love each other so much, maybe too much, so they rather surfer alone to let the other one be happy. Ross has a major crush on Rachel for years, it began since middle school, but never told Rachael before. When Rachael ran away from her wedding at pilot, the crush is back. But he never got the courage to tell her, there’s always an Italia guy or ex fiancé get in the way. By the time she found out Ross’ already flew to China, but Ross flew back from China with his new girlfriend Julie. Though wanting him so much, she kept silent about this, because Ross is so happy with Julie. After Ross and Rachael made out, Joey ask what’s cons about Julie to help him clear his thought, Ross answers, “she’s not Rachael”. Yeah, that’s the problem, he only loves Rachael. When Rachael saw the tape what Ross’ve done for her years ago on the prom night, they hug and kiss passionately, all the audience applauded and shouting, my tears couldn’t help neither. Two years later, during these times, they’ve broken up, at Ross and Emily’s wedding, Rachael showed up. Flying a long way to tell Ross she’s still in love with him, but seeing Ross so happy about his Wedding, instead, she says, “Congratulation.” With Rachael’s heart broken, mine breaks too. But later, Ross said Rachael’s name at the altar, I know for sure, it’s wrong for Ross marrying someone not Rachael. In Vegas, they got drunken and married, but Rachael’s not sure there’s the right thing they’ve done, then required a divorce. I don’t feel sorry for this, it’s the right thing to do, I don’t want them marry each other because a drunken decision, they should marry for the real reason-true love. At the ending of last episode, right before Rachael leave, she thought all their history clear and run off the plane. The processing is so much more important than the consequence. If say so, during all ten years (if counting those years in middle school there’s more), Ross and Rachael using most of time defining what’s the relationship between them., you might says that’s kind of sentimental. This is not. All those defining and redefining is what make their story meaningful, they kept giving others the best in their life, even it means many days and nights being along missing other. That’s true love. In our modern love lives, we tend to ask too much from a relationship but hardly willing to give up anything. Maybe that’s why divorce rate kept growing. Watching Friends, even years after it ended, we can still learn so much from it. my very first review, thx for reading. your criticism can help my writing get better
